            {
              "w": "a. We have learn that the tanwin is the indefinite article, e.g. بَيْتٌ a house. The rule does not apply to proper nouns. So حَامِدٌ is just \"hamid\", not \"a hamid\".\n\nb. Feminine proper nouns have no tanwin, e.g. فَاطِمَةُ،  زَزْنَبُ،  آمِنَةُ "
